# Visual Era — two env files (gitignored copies hold your secrets)
#
#  LOCAL (development)     →  .env.local
#  LIVE  (production)      →  .env.production.local
#
# First time:
#   cp .env.local.example .env.local
#   cp .env.production.local.example .env.production.local
#
# Or split an existing single .env:
#   npm run env:setup
#
# Refresh both from .env (overwrites):
#   npm run env:refresh
#
# Templates: .env.local.example · .env.production.local.example
# Docs:      docs/ops/LOCAL_ENV.md
